A man was stabbed to death during the early hours of yesterday. The unidentified man was found dead in Durban Road, Korsten, at about 1.30am. Police spokeswoman Captain Sandra Janse van Rensburg said bystanders had alerted police when they saw the man collapse on the side of the road. They initially thought the man was drunk, but a passer-by noticed blood and discovered he had been stabbed in the chest. He was declared dead at the scene. The man s wallet appeared to be missing. Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share